oc:kn_2c1d4392 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When initiating a competitive analysis engagement" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always request company/product context, specific competitor names, industry/market segment, geographic scope, and focus areas before starting analysis. More context yields more actionable output." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Competitive analysis without context produces generic, low-value output; specificity drives relevance." .

oc:kn_2fee9870 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting expectations for competitive analysis output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cannot access competitor internal data, real-time pricing, proprietary market research, or continuously monitor competitor activity. Analysis is based solely on publicly available information." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Competitive analysis is inherently limited to public data; users must understand the scope boundary to avoid over-relying on potentially stale or incomplete intelligence." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4c318f9c a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting analysis framework" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Match analysis type to the user's purpose: Quick Comparison for feature/pricing matrices, Full Profile for deep-dives, Strategic Analysis for SWOT and positioning, Battle Card for sales enablement." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different business needs require different depths and formats of competitive intelligence." .

oc:kn_78da5b51 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conducting full or strategic competitive analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use Porter's four-dimension framework (Future Goals, Current Strategy, Assumptions, Capabilities) to build a Competitor Response Profile that predicts competitor behavior, vulnerabilities, and retaliation triggers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured frameworks ensure comprehensive coverage and prevent blind spots in competitor assessment." .

oc:kn_b6160eee a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Running the same competitive analysis at different times will produce different results due to market dynamics and data availability. Reports should be timestamped." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Competitive intelligence is inherently non-deterministic; market conditions change continuously." .

oc:kn_cd1a4121 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When validating completeness of output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A successful competitive analysis includes: executive summary with key takeaways, competitor profiles with strengths/weaknesses, feature comparison matrix, pricing comparison, positioning map, SWOT summary, strategic recommendations, and optionally battle cards." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Comprehensive reports enable better strategic decisions by covering all relevant competitive dimensions." .

oc:kn_e3b3e5df a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When delivering any competitive analysis report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never present competitive analysis findings without noting that data is time-sensitive and should be verified before strategic decisions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Competitive intelligence degrades quickly; unverified data can lead to misguided strategic decisions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

